cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to detect incongruity between news headlines and body text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract relevant information from news articles, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The use of neural networks and deep learning models suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with the detection of misleading news, which could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
